1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
{\an8}<b><font color="#9CD5FF">One Pace Premium</font></b>
Keep the project alive: <font color="#a8c7fa">ko-fi.com/not6ip</font>

2
00:01:57,420 --> 00:02:03,010
This is the Grand Line's Gloom Island,
the ruins of the Muggy Kingdom.

3
00:02:06,060 --> 00:02:10,310
In the old castle near the lake
of this fallen country,

4
00:02:10,350 --> 00:02:12,770
lives a certain man...

5
00:02:17,650 --> 00:02:19,490
A Warlord of the Sea...

6
00:02:19,490 --> 00:02:21,700
and the world's greatest swordsman.

7
00:02:21,700 --> 00:02:25,410
His name is Dracule Mihawk.

8
00:02:35,500 --> 00:02:37,800
Master Moria...

9
00:02:44,510 --> 00:02:47,020
He's... alive...

10
00:02:48,310 --> 00:02:53,020
“Gecko Moria and His Zombie Army Attack”...

11
00:02:54,020 --> 00:02:55,980
He's alive!

12
00:02:56,030 --> 00:02:59,740
Master Moria is really alive!

13
00:03:00,240 --> 00:03:05,490
Look! It's amazing! Master Moria is alive!

14
00:03:07,450 --> 00:03:09,460
Yes, I read it this morning.

15
00:03:09,910 --> 00:03:14,500
And you didn't think to tell me, you jerk?!
This is very important to me!

16
00:03:14,500 --> 00:03:15,460
I don't care.

17
00:03:15,460 --> 00:03:18,340
You should! He's my captain!

18
00:03:18,880 --> 00:03:22,760
I thought he died in
the Summit War two years ago!

19
00:03:22,760 --> 00:03:24,430
I'm so relieved!

20
00:03:25,800 --> 00:03:31,770
If Master Moria is alive,
maybe Absalom and Hogback are with him!

21
00:03:32,560 --> 00:03:36,020
I just have to see him now!
Let's get a move on!

22
00:03:44,280 --> 00:03:46,030
Oh, yeah...

23
00:03:46,780 --> 00:03:49,910
He let me stay here for ages.

24
00:03:53,250 --> 00:03:56,670
Ever since Bartholomew Kuma
interrupted my confrontation with

25
00:03:56,670 --> 00:03:59,590
the Straw Hats at Thriller Bark
and sent me flying here.

26
00:04:00,050 --> 00:04:02,130
So it's already been two years...

27
00:04:03,340 --> 00:04:08,350
Moria is as tenacious as
the zombies he commands.

28
00:04:08,760 --> 00:04:11,310
Huh? Are you making fun of Master Moria?!

29
00:04:11,310 --> 00:04:12,890
You ungrateful jerk!

30
00:04:14,060 --> 00:04:15,270
I owe him nothing.

31
00:04:15,270 --> 00:04:17,060
You owe me!

32
00:04:17,560 --> 00:04:20,320
Do you know how many times
I cooked for you?!

33
00:04:21,360 --> 00:04:23,400
I cooked more than you did.

34
00:04:23,400 --> 00:04:25,860
I helped with the farming, too!

35
00:04:26,320 --> 00:04:28,160
I let you stay here.

36
00:04:30,080 --> 00:04:32,080
You're so annoying!

37
00:04:32,080 --> 00:04:33,080
Fine!

38
00:04:41,920 --> 00:04:42,630
I'm leaving!

39
00:04:43,340 --> 00:04:44,300
As you wish.

40
00:04:46,180 --> 00:04:48,720
I'm glad nothing's keeping me tied here.

41
00:04:51,100 --> 00:04:52,930
Take care of yourself.

42
00:05:05,200 --> 00:05:06,610
Now you're nice?!

43
00:05:06,610 --> 00:05:10,780
Damn you! Don't spring
those kind words on me!

44
00:05:19,250 --> 00:05:22,210
Thank you for everything!

45
00:05:24,380 --> 00:05:26,340
Such a noisome woman.

46
00:05:26,930 --> 00:05:27,630
But...

47
00:05:29,300 --> 00:05:33,310
the timing of your departure
is likely fortuitous.

48
00:05:33,310 --> 00:05:34,350
What?

49
00:05:37,810 --> 00:05:40,860
The Reverie at Mary Geoise
is currently underway...

50
00:05:42,610 --> 00:05:44,990
during which an odd topic has arisen.

51
00:06:10,840 --> 00:06:12,720
Charge!

52
00:06:35,830 --> 00:06:38,750
Where's Absalom?!

53
00:06:38,750 --> 00:06:42,080
Where are you hiding him?!

54
00:07:03,810 --> 00:07:06,110
Why can't I kill them?!

55
00:07:12,160 --> 00:07:15,030
Where's Absalom?!

56
00:07:15,030 --> 00:07:16,620
I don't know!

57
00:07:17,950 --> 00:07:20,660
None of you grunts know a damn thing!

58
00:07:22,670 --> 00:07:24,330
Where's Blackbeard?!

59
00:07:24,330 --> 00:07:28,170
Where is he?! Bring me Teach!

60
00:07:28,170 --> 00:07:30,420
Don't mess with us!

61
00:07:31,300 --> 00:07:33,970
Didn't you hear what I said?!

62
00:07:34,010 --> 00:07:36,890
I said, bring me Teach!

63
00:07:37,510 --> 00:07:40,850
Teach! Where are you?!

64
00:07:40,850 --> 00:07:43,600
It's gotten noisy-meow.

65
00:07:45,400 --> 00:07:47,980
It's Gecko Moria, Captain Pizarro!

66
00:07:48,400 --> 00:07:50,690
The former Warlord of the Sea!

67
00:07:50,690 --> 00:07:53,950
Oh, why did you let him in?

68
00:07:53,950 --> 00:07:57,910
H-He broke in! With his zombie army!

69
00:07:57,910 --> 00:07:59,870
The port is in ruins!

70
00:08:00,290 --> 00:08:02,790
What does he want?

71
00:08:07,380 --> 00:08:09,460
He wants to see Commodore Teach!

72
00:08:09,460 --> 00:08:14,590
Seems like he's looking for Absalom,
the invisible man that came here recently.

73
00:08:16,600 --> 00:08:18,010
Oh, him!

74
00:08:18,010 --> 00:08:21,060
If you're not coming out,

75
00:08:21,060 --> 00:08:24,480
I'm gonna bust in!

76
00:08:24,730 --> 00:08:26,610
Master Moria!

77
00:08:28,400 --> 00:08:31,860
I'm here!

78
00:08:32,440 --> 00:08:34,530
Is that you, Absalom?!

79
00:08:34,530 --> 00:08:38,080
Boss! It's me!

80
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:41,620
Thank goodness! You're alive!

81
00:08:42,450 --> 00:08:45,250
I'm as good as new!

82
00:08:45,250 --> 00:08:50,670
We didn't hear from you after we parted ways,

83
00:08:50,670 --> 00:08:53,220
so we got worried!

84
00:08:53,880 --> 00:08:58,350
I'm sorry, Boss! It's just that
this island is a paradise!

85
00:08:58,350 --> 00:09:03,520
I was having so much fun that
I forgot to keep in touch!

86
00:09:07,440 --> 00:09:10,860
Well, that sounds like reason enough for me!

87
00:09:10,860 --> 00:09:12,110
But...

88
00:09:12,570 --> 00:09:15,570
it looks like I went a little overboard...

89
00:09:16,410 --> 00:09:19,320
Zombies, that's enough!

90
00:09:19,320 --> 00:09:20,950
Go back to the ship!

91
00:09:26,080 --> 00:09:31,670
The Blackbeard Pirates are known
for hunting people with abilities!

92
00:09:33,010 --> 00:09:34,420
That's right.

93
00:09:34,420 --> 00:09:41,640
The powers of your Clear-Clear Fruit
are very desirable...

94
00:09:43,720 --> 00:09:46,560
since it allows you to become invisible.

95
00:09:46,560 --> 00:09:49,060
I know that, too...

96
00:09:49,730 --> 00:09:51,650
very well...

97
00:09:55,990 --> 00:09:56,990
What the...?!

98
00:10:02,530 --> 00:10:05,410
Ouch! Damn it!

99
00:10:05,410 --> 00:10:06,910
Who did that?!

100
00:10:07,460 --> 00:10:09,580
Where are you?!

101
00:10:23,140 --> 00:10:25,350
Do you know who I am?

102
00:10:26,020 --> 00:10:29,480
Shiryu... of the Rain!

103
00:10:30,600 --> 00:10:34,150
You're that Impel Down dog
that defected to Teach!

104
00:10:35,570 --> 00:10:37,610
You got the gist of it.

105
00:10:45,240 --> 00:10:48,500
Do you like my power?

106
00:10:51,540 --> 00:10:53,960
You were invisible!

107
00:10:56,550 --> 00:11:00,050
That power belongs to Absalom...

108
00:11:04,050 --> 00:11:06,390
No way...!

109
00:11:06,770 --> 00:11:11,350
Your suspicion is warranted, Gecko Moria.

110
00:11:12,190 --> 00:11:14,270
I've acquired a useful ability.

111
00:11:16,650 --> 00:11:18,900
Damn...

112
00:11:18,900 --> 00:11:23,240
Dammit!

113
00:11:27,290 --> 00:11:31,370
Then, who the hell are you?!

114
00:11:45,180 --> 00:11:46,390
Devon!

115
00:12:01,320 --> 00:12:03,910
– Captain Devon!
– Captain Devon!

116
00:12:05,950 --> 00:12:09,700
Don't tell me Absalom is...

117
00:12:10,370 --> 00:12:15,000
He shouldn't have come here so recklessly!

118
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:18,630
We still have his body if you want it.

119
00:12:19,500 --> 00:12:22,800
You're fond of corpses, right?

120
00:12:26,600 --> 00:12:32,270
Damn you guys! I won't forgive you!

121
00:12:32,350 --> 00:12:36,610
How dare you kill my friend?!

122
00:12:36,610 --> 00:12:41,740
I'll turn you all into corpses!

123
00:12:41,740 --> 00:12:45,570
Oh, I'd like to see you try.

124
00:13:09,010 --> 00:13:14,140
Don't disturb the peace here on Pirate Island!

125
00:13:14,140 --> 00:13:16,060
That voice...!

126
00:13:16,060 --> 00:13:19,650
Screw you! Show yourself!

127
00:13:20,070 --> 00:13:22,480
No way!

128
00:13:22,480 --> 00:13:25,360
I'm relaxing now.

129
00:13:26,320 --> 00:13:29,990
This is a paradise for pirates!

130
00:13:30,580 --> 00:13:33,620
It oughta be fun!

131
00:13:34,120 --> 00:13:35,750
You guys!

132
00:13:36,250 --> 00:13:38,710
Do you like to party?!

133
00:13:46,130 --> 00:13:48,050
If so,

134
00:13:48,050 --> 00:13:51,100
come aboard my ship!

135
00:14:04,690 --> 00:14:06,780
Moria!

136
00:14:07,200 --> 00:14:09,950
Don't you like...

137
00:14:09,950 --> 00:14:12,240
to party?!

138
00:14:31,600 --> 00:14:33,720
Did you read the morning paper?

139
00:14:35,520 --> 00:14:38,060
There's never a dull moment!

140
00:14:39,310 --> 00:14:42,270
On the fourth day of the Reverie...

141
00:14:42,270 --> 00:14:44,980
the commanders of the Revolutionary Army...

142
00:14:44,980 --> 00:14:49,860
burst into the Sacred Mary
Geoise to take back Kuma,

143
00:14:49,860 --> 00:14:56,200
and clashed with Marine Admirals
Ryokugyu and Fujitora!

144
00:14:58,500 --> 00:15:00,790
Meanwhile...

145
00:15:01,420 --> 00:15:05,380
in Wano where the monstrous Kaido resides...

146
00:15:06,170 --> 00:15:08,590
the arrival of Straw Hat...

147
00:15:08,630 --> 00:15:12,090
and a bunch of other hot-blooded
punks has made headlines.

148
00:15:12,890 --> 00:15:15,310
And chasing them is...

149
00:15:15,310 --> 00:15:20,020
the mad Emperor Big Mom!

150
00:15:24,900 --> 00:15:26,610
What do you think will happen?!

151
00:15:33,160 --> 00:15:36,160
It's already begun.

152
00:15:36,240 --> 00:15:38,790
In order to sit on the throne...

153
00:15:38,790 --> 00:15:43,290
the mighty will crush one another!

154
00:18:06,350 --> 00:18:08,560
He's as strong as Duke Inuarashi!

155
00:18:08,560 --> 00:18:12,860
That he can give Duke Inuarashi a run
for his money... How impressive...

156
00:18:13,440 --> 00:18:15,410
Why, Ashura?

157
00:18:15,410 --> 00:18:21,530
Why not use that tremendous power
for Kuri, for Lord Oden's beloved people?!

158
00:18:30,630 --> 00:18:33,210
He's dead!

159
00:18:33,210 --> 00:18:37,420
Why did you guys even bother
coming back after all this time?!

160
00:18:37,420 --> 00:18:40,720
We came back to fulfill Lord Oden's dream!

161
00:18:40,720 --> 00:18:45,350
But you-gara have forgotten
what happened to Lord Oden

162
00:18:45,350 --> 00:18:48,060
and are doing as you please with your sword!

163
00:18:48,060 --> 00:18:49,690
Shut up!

164
00:18:58,440 --> 00:19:02,280
Don't talk as if you know everything!

165
00:19:02,910 --> 00:19:05,990
If there is something you
want to say, then say it!

166
00:19:11,250 --> 00:19:14,540
Foxfire Style: Fire-Willow Flash!

167
00:19:24,600 --> 00:19:25,850
Gentlemen...

168
00:19:27,770 --> 00:19:29,810
That's enough.

169
00:19:31,060 --> 00:19:32,100
Inuarashi!

170
00:19:32,810 --> 00:19:33,860
Ashura!

171
00:19:42,360 --> 00:19:45,070
I thought you were better than this, Ashura!

172
00:19:47,740 --> 00:19:49,200
Kiku!

173
00:19:49,620 --> 00:19:55,500
I've watched Wano since
Lord Oden died two decades ago.

174
00:19:55,500 --> 00:20:00,420
You all think you can
show up now and preach to me?

175
00:20:00,420 --> 00:20:01,380
I won't listen!

176
00:20:04,970 --> 00:20:09,970
You should be thankful I'm not
robbing you blind before I go!

177
00:20:10,520 --> 00:20:12,020
Don't you remember?!

178
00:20:12,440 --> 00:20:15,650
This is how we were even back then!

179
00:20:16,560 --> 00:20:21,320
I was fascinated by that man, Kozuki Oden.

180
00:20:21,320 --> 00:20:26,120
I risked my life for him as a samurai!

181
00:20:26,120 --> 00:20:30,910
But I never pledged to support
the rest of the Kozuki clan!

182
00:20:33,210 --> 00:20:34,080
Right...

183
00:20:35,380 --> 00:20:37,090
Momonosuke?

184
00:20:48,760 --> 00:20:53,940
Then I suggest you remember
the kind of man that I was!

185
00:20:55,060 --> 00:20:57,020
I won't give up!

186
00:20:58,060 --> 00:20:59,770
I'll have you join us!

187
00:21:01,730 --> 00:21:08,200
Don't assume that everyone will be thrilled
to see the return of the Kozuki Clan's samurai!

188
00:21:11,870 --> 00:21:17,000
You guys abandoned the country
for twenty years!

189
00:21:17,750 --> 00:21:20,340
You will never make up for that lost time!

190
00:21:30,720 --> 00:21:32,520
Are you hurt?

191
00:21:32,520 --> 00:21:33,680
No.

192
00:21:34,480 --> 00:21:35,350
Let's go.

193
00:21:38,060 --> 00:21:40,020
I am sorry to interrupt you.

194
00:21:40,020 --> 00:21:41,020
Raizo...!

195
00:21:41,020 --> 00:21:44,530
I was able to locate Sir Luffy.

196
00:21:44,530 --> 00:21:47,700
He is at the prisoner mining camp in Udon.

197
00:21:47,700 --> 00:21:52,200
I thought so! Then, I am
counting on you to handle it.

198
00:21:52,200 --> 00:21:53,540
Understood!

199
00:22:00,880 --> 00:22:03,000
Otama! Are you awake?!

200
00:22:05,510 --> 00:22:09,260
Master, what happened to me?

201
00:22:09,800 --> 00:22:15,930
You were attacked by Kaido,
but these people treated you!

202
00:22:17,560 --> 00:22:19,600
Oh, I see.

203
00:22:19,600 --> 00:22:21,560
Thank you!

204
00:22:21,560 --> 00:22:23,190
I am grateful!

205
00:22:23,190 --> 00:22:26,690
Your injuries were minor.
You'll get better soon!

206
00:22:26,690 --> 00:22:28,490
Thanks!

207
00:22:32,160 --> 00:22:36,500
I was so scared, I just passed out.

208
00:22:36,500 --> 00:22:41,880
I don't really remember the attack.

209
00:22:42,420 --> 00:22:46,210
I kinda remember Horsella fighting real hard...

210
00:22:48,720 --> 00:22:50,930
Where to, Master?!

211
00:22:56,020 --> 00:22:59,940
An enemy became that loyal to you?

212
00:22:59,940 --> 00:23:01,600
What an astonishing power!

213
00:23:01,600 --> 00:23:05,150
What happened to Horsella
and Big Bro?! Are they okay?!

214
00:23:06,030 --> 00:23:09,110
We don't know what happened to Horsella...

215
00:23:10,320 --> 00:23:11,530
But Luffy was...

216
00:23:19,910 --> 00:23:20,790
What?!

217
00:23:21,370 --> 00:23:24,000
Big Bro was pretty badly hurt...

218
00:23:24,420 --> 00:23:26,550
and taken to the mine in Udon?!

219
00:23:27,420 --> 00:23:28,800
Oh no!

220
00:23:28,800 --> 00:23:30,510
Hey, you're wounded!

221
00:23:30,510 --> 00:23:34,890
I'm more worried about
Big Bro Luffy than my wounds!

222
00:23:34,890 --> 00:23:39,270
He'll be fine! Luffy's our captain!

223
00:23:41,100 --> 00:23:44,610
Udon is a region of Wano.

224
00:23:44,610 --> 00:23:50,240
These days, it is mostly known
for the prisoner mining camp.

225
00:23:51,530 --> 00:23:55,700
It's a dreadful place where serious offenders

226
00:23:55,700 --> 00:23:59,360
are forced to perform hard labor until they die.

227
00:23:59,360 --> 00:24:01,290
No one has ever escaped.

228
00:24:16,890 --> 00:24:19,310
No, we don't need any geisha.

229
00:24:19,310 --> 00:24:22,310
Don't let anyone near this room!

230
00:24:22,310 --> 00:24:23,350
Yes, sir!

231
00:24:44,670 --> 00:24:48,380
You're bad...!

232
00:24:54,510 --> 00:24:58,930
Here's the order for armor and weapons.

233
00:24:58,930 --> 00:25:01,680
You're definitely bad!

234
00:25:02,980 --> 00:25:04,560
Huh? Am I?

235
00:25:04,980 --> 00:25:09,690
Oh, this is a lot! Is there
going to be a war or something?

236
00:25:09,690 --> 00:25:12,280
We don't know what's happening abroad.

237
00:25:12,280 --> 00:25:15,240
We just make whatever they want.

238
00:25:15,240 --> 00:25:18,280
You're so, so bad!

239
00:25:20,160 --> 00:25:21,410
Huh? Am I?

240
00:25:21,410 --> 00:25:25,080
Look closely, Onami.
My old eyes can't handle this.

241
00:25:25,540 --> 00:25:28,460
You're doing great!
Keep calm while you watch.

242
00:25:29,750 --> 00:25:31,630
His head is blocking my view.

243
00:25:33,840 --> 00:25:35,090
Somebody's there!

244
00:25:35,720 --> 00:25:36,470
Who is it?!

245
00:25:47,440 --> 00:25:48,440
Who are they?!

246
00:25:52,400 --> 00:25:53,990
Search the attic!

247
00:25:53,990 --> 00:25:56,030
Catch them at any cost!

248
00:25:57,910 --> 00:26:00,280
Calm down, Shinobu!

249
00:26:00,280 --> 00:26:01,620
You're not getting away!

250
00:26:10,250 --> 00:26:11,920
Be quiet!

251
00:26:12,750 --> 00:26:14,340
Where did they go?!

252
00:26:19,970 --> 00:26:22,100
Oh, is it just a cat?

253
00:27:02,220 --> 00:27:03,760
Where'd they go?!

254
00:27:14,900 --> 00:27:17,360
What's the matter with you, Shinobu?!

255
00:27:22,700 --> 00:27:23,910
Are you okay?

256
00:27:27,040 --> 00:27:28,290
Onami...

257
00:27:28,700 --> 00:27:30,790
there's something I haven't told you.

258
00:27:30,790 --> 00:27:31,960
What?

259
00:27:34,290 --> 00:27:37,300
Find them! Catch them!

260
00:27:37,710 --> 00:27:40,300
Don't let the intruders get away!

261
00:27:46,760 --> 00:27:48,100
I'm...

262
00:27:50,850 --> 00:27:52,980
afraid of sharp objects!

263
00:28:00,740 --> 00:28:03,160
You're not cut out for any kind of fight then!

264
00:28:03,700 --> 00:28:05,530
But Onami...

265
00:28:08,040 --> 00:28:09,750
a mature woman...

266
00:28:10,500 --> 00:28:12,290
is a deadly...

267
00:28:13,210 --> 00:28:14,790
weapon.

268
00:28:22,260 --> 00:28:24,840
Let's catch this wind.

269
00:28:24,840 --> 00:28:25,550
What?

270
00:28:28,630 --> 00:28:30,890
Ninpo: Great Kite!

271
00:28:43,610 --> 00:28:46,700
Shinobu, this is amazing!

272
00:28:48,410 --> 00:28:51,080
Haven't you found them yet?!

273
00:28:54,170 --> 00:28:56,920
What did you see in the residence, Onami?

274
00:28:56,920 --> 00:28:58,880
Um...

275
00:28:58,880 --> 00:29:02,260
Oh! I saw the name of the port
and the shipment day!

276
00:29:02,260 --> 00:29:04,050
Well done!

277
00:29:04,050 --> 00:29:06,840
Now we know when and where
their weapons will arrive...

278
00:29:07,260 --> 00:29:08,720
so we can steal them!

279
00:29:09,310 --> 00:29:10,260
Uh-huh!

280
00:29:22,280 --> 00:29:25,280
Look! Something's happening in town.

281
00:29:25,910 --> 00:29:27,570
What's that line for?

282
00:29:28,070 --> 00:29:29,410
Is it a sale?!

283
00:29:29,410 --> 00:29:31,330
There are so many young ladies.

284
00:29:32,750 --> 00:29:36,460
Welcome! Welcome!

285
00:29:41,880 --> 00:29:45,590
Ladies, step right up and have a bite!

286
00:29:47,220 --> 00:29:49,680
And of course that voice belongs to...

287
00:29:55,560 --> 00:29:58,150
It's sweet when it melts in your mouth.

288
00:30:00,190 --> 00:30:02,440
That's al dente for you.

289
00:30:05,440 --> 00:30:06,780
Sangoro's...

290
00:30:07,150 --> 00:30:08,530
nihachi soba!

291
00:30:11,530 --> 00:30:13,830
Three, five, two, eight!

292
00:30:13,830 --> 00:30:16,460
The sum is the special number eighteen!

293
00:30:24,210 --> 00:30:26,300
It's my special soba!

294
00:30:27,340 --> 00:30:29,090
The noodles shine!

295
00:30:29,130 --> 00:30:30,590
They're so chewy!

296
00:30:30,590 --> 00:30:33,310
– It's delicious!
– It's delicious!

297
00:30:33,310 --> 00:30:35,770
Recruit some samurai already!

298
00:30:35,770 --> 00:30:38,060
Thank you!

299
00:30:39,940 --> 00:30:42,400
Troubling news!

300
00:30:42,400 --> 00:30:45,780
Ghosts are appearing to curse us!

301
00:30:45,780 --> 00:30:50,030
Ghost sightings at the northern
graveyard! Here's an update!

302
00:30:51,120 --> 00:30:53,080
Oh? What's happening here?

303
00:30:53,080 --> 00:30:55,080
I'll take a look.

304
00:30:59,960 --> 00:31:02,000
Kamazo "the Reaper"?

305
00:31:17,520 --> 00:31:19,180
It's him!

306
00:31:22,650 --> 00:31:28,490
If you see him, that means you're
already dead! How blood-chilling!

307
00:31:28,900 --> 00:31:31,360
Who is he really?!

308
00:31:32,530 --> 00:31:35,870
My husband was killed by him, too!

309
00:31:35,870 --> 00:31:38,660
Now, gather 'round! Gather 'round!

310
00:31:38,660 --> 00:31:44,080
There's also news about the Witching Hour Boy,
who appears at the third hour after midnight!

311
00:31:44,080 --> 00:31:46,300
He's a thief who steals from the rich...

312
00:31:46,300 --> 00:31:50,220
and gives to the poor living
in tenement houses!

313
00:31:50,220 --> 00:31:53,550
Is he a hero or a villain?!

314
00:31:53,550 --> 00:31:56,220
What is his true identity?!

315
00:31:56,220 --> 00:31:59,270
If you want to know, buy a notice paper!

316
00:31:59,270 --> 00:32:01,520
Ah! Sir Witching Hour!

317
00:32:01,520 --> 00:32:02,900
I'll take one!

318
00:32:02,900 --> 00:32:04,020
Yes, thank you!

319
00:32:04,020 --> 00:32:05,650
Come and get your own!

320
00:32:05,650 --> 00:32:08,610
This notice paper is filled with exclusives!

321
00:32:08,610 --> 00:32:10,450
I'll take one, too!

322
00:32:10,450 --> 00:32:11,570
Me, too!

323
00:32:25,710 --> 00:32:27,460
The reversed crescent moon!

324
00:32:30,800 --> 00:32:31,880
Who gave me this?

325
00:33:17,050 --> 00:33:19,510
Are they really back?!

326
00:33:28,770 --> 00:33:30,520
– The Kozuki Clan!
– The Kozuki Clan!

327
00:33:40,530 --> 00:33:43,870
Hey, this could be the work of those ghosts.

328
00:33:43,870 --> 00:33:47,210
Suspicion will get us nowhere!
This will spark a great fire!

329
00:33:50,420 --> 00:33:51,800
I'm going!

330
00:33:53,550 --> 00:33:58,300
If this were ten years ago,
I would have fought...

331
00:33:59,140 --> 00:34:02,390
But what are you all going to do for weapons?

332
00:34:03,930 --> 00:34:07,770
This country prohibits all but samurai
from carrying weapons.

333
00:34:09,100 --> 00:34:11,360
All the kendo halls have closed down.

334
00:34:11,360 --> 00:34:16,030
Martial arts like karate
and judo are also prohibited.

335
00:34:16,030 --> 00:34:19,490
Orochi has already stamped out
the spark of rebellion.

336
00:34:20,280 --> 00:34:23,040
I'll fight even if it's with my bare hands!

337
00:34:23,040 --> 00:34:27,500
This will be our last chance!
I've been waiting for so long!

338
00:34:27,500 --> 00:34:28,920
I can't stop...

339
00:34:29,630 --> 00:34:31,790
trembling with excitement!

340
00:35:02,200 --> 00:35:03,080
Sir Luffy.

341
00:35:03,080 --> 00:35:04,700
Raizo!

342
00:35:05,200 --> 00:35:06,750
Not so loud!

343
00:35:08,790 --> 00:35:09,830
What's wrong?

344
00:35:10,710 --> 00:35:14,130
Nothing. I actually have good news.

345
00:35:14,840 --> 00:35:16,960
Otama is better.

346
00:35:17,670 --> 00:35:19,880
Oh! She is?!

347
00:35:28,020 --> 00:35:29,560
Okay, I'll be back later.

348
00:35:29,600 --> 00:35:30,440
Okay.

349
00:35:31,230 --> 00:35:33,480
Ya-hoo!

350
00:35:45,030 --> 00:35:46,080
Hey, Jack...

351
00:35:47,200 --> 00:35:49,290
the revenue from Kuri is pathetic.

352
00:35:56,040 --> 00:35:57,880
Now that Doflamingo's not around...

353
00:35:58,340 --> 00:36:02,090
you know who our next business
partner is, don't you?!

354
00:36:02,590 --> 00:36:04,970
I'm sorry, Brothers...

355
00:36:10,020 --> 00:36:13,600
We don't need more deadweight
than this idiot Queen.

356
00:36:14,400 --> 00:36:19,070
That's right! You don't need
more scum when you've got King.

357
00:36:24,320 --> 00:36:27,330
– Got that, Jack the stooge?!
– Got that, Jack the stooge?!

358
00:36:30,950 --> 00:36:33,210
And you, Queen!

359
00:36:34,120 --> 00:36:39,800
Why is it taking so long to break those brats?!

360
00:36:39,800 --> 00:36:41,260
You no-account bum!

361
00:36:41,260 --> 00:36:44,970
Shut it, you sadistic pervert!

